title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield SAR-8 (HK-91 by Helenic Arms, Greece
postcontent: IN Tyler, TX 21-25 December. This is a Springfield SAR-8 sporter made in Greece. This is not to be confused with the newer (and vastly inferior) SAR-8 sold by Springfield with the cast aluminum receiver, this is all steel receiver, and not some parts kit build. These are HK-91 clones made on HK tooling set-up by HK engineers, made by HK trained technicians at Hellenic Arms. These were imported by Springfield as SAR-3 for a while before being caught up in the early assault weapon ban. Springfield slapped a thumb hole stock on them, pinned and welded a non flash suppressor on them and overstamped the SAR-3 with an SAR-8. The quality on these is felt to be second only to HK since everything was set-up by them. Included are 3x 20rd steel magazines, 5x 20 rd aluminum magazines, and the original 5 rd magazine. This rifle does have some small handling marks but I would say it is still in very good condition. It has been kept in a safe and very well taken care of. I'm parting with it because my interests have changed and I need to make room for some other projects. TX drivers license and bill of sale required for transaction, prefer CHL. title: For Sale/Trade:  """COLLECTORS"""LONE RANGER SILVER BULLET
postcontent:
REMINGTON REA LONE RANGER 45 COLT SILVER BULLET	

Here is a unique cartridge in Remington production. In the 1960’s REA (the old Railway Express Agency, eventually put out of business by UPS) came up with a marketing scheme capitalizing on the fame/concept of the Lone Ranger and the silver bullets he would leave as a memento of his saving someone’s skin. REA delivery people were supposed to be the modern day Ranger saving people’s businesses by their rapid deliveries and would leave this cartridge behind as a momento of their efforts. Its special headstamp is HI-YO REA AWAAAY and was created with a holed DUMMY primer, nickel plated .45 Colt case. A very special round for your Remington or Lone Ranger collection. Thanks for looking
